tionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from Middle English <i>brigge</i> ‘bridge’, Old English <i>brycg</i>, applied as a topographic name for someone who lived near a bridge, a metonymic occupational name for a bridge keeper, or a habitational name from any of the places called with this element, as for example Bridge in Kent or Bridge Sollers in Herefordshire. Building and maintaining bridges was one of the three main feudal obligations, along with bearing arms and maintaining fortifications. The cost of building a bridge was often defrayed by charging a toll, the surname thus being acquired by the toll gatherer."],"variants":[{"name":"Bridges","meanings":["English: variant of   Bridge  . The <i>-s</i> generally represents the genitive case, but may occasionally be a plural. In some cases this name denoted someone from the Flemish city of Bruges (Brugge) in Belgium, meaning ‘bridges’, which had extensive trading links with England in the Middle Ages."]},{"name":"Bridger","meanings":["English: from an agent derivative of Middle English <i>brigge</i>, <i>brugge</i> ‘bridge’ (Old English <i>brycg</i>), denoting either someone who lived near a bridge or the keeper of a bridge. See   Bridge  .","Americanized form of German <b>Brücker</b> (see   Brucker  )."]},{"name":"Burge","meanings":["English: variant of   Bridge  , Old English <i>brycg</i>, with metathesis of <i>u</i> and <i>r</i>, as exemplified in several placenames of this origin in various parts of southern England.","Swiss German and German (<b>Bürge</b>): from Middle High German <i>bürge</i> ‘bailsman, guarantor’. Compare   Buerge  ."]},{"name":"Bridgeman","meanings":["English: topographic or occupational name from Middle English <i>brigge</i>, <i>brugge</i> ‘bridge’ (Old English <i>brycg</i>) + <i>man</i>, denoting either a dweller by or a keeper of a bridge. See   Bridge  .","In some cases possibly also an Americanized form (translation into English) of German <b>Bruckmann</b> (see   Bruckman  ).","History: James Bridgeman or Bridgman (1620–76) came to Hartford, CT, from Winchester, Hampshire, England, in 1640."]},{"name":"Brugman","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Helmut, Erna, Kurt.","Dutch: topographic name for someone who lived near a bridge or a metonymic occupational name for a bridge keeper, from Dutch <i>brug</i> ‘bridge’ (see   Bridge  ). Compare   Bruggeman  .","Americanized form of Swiss German <b>Bruggmann</b> ‘bridge keeper’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Bridge was born about 1540 as the son of Bridge. He had at least 1 son."},"et":{"about 1540–":"umbes 1540–Surnud","1540–Male":"1540–Surnud","1560–Male":"1560–Surnud","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","about 1540":"umbes 1540"},"fi":{"about 1540–":"noin 1540–Kuollut","1540–Male":"1540–Kuollut","1560–Male":"1560–Kuollut","1520–Male":"1520–Kuollut","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","about 1540":"noin 1540"},"fr":{"about 1540–":"environ 1540–Décédé","1540–Male":"1540–Décédé","1560–Male":"1560–Décédé","1520–Male":"1520–Décédé","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","about 1540":"environ 1540","lifeSummary":"Bridge est né environ 1540, fils de Bridge. Il a eu au moins 1 fils."},"de":{"about 1540–":"um 1540–Verstorben","1540–Male":"1540–Verstorben","1560–Male":"1560–Verstorben","1520–Male":"1520–Verstorben","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","about 1540":"um 1540","lifeSummary":"Bridge wurde um 1540, als Sohn von Bridge geboren. Er hatte mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"about 1540–":"about 1540–Desede","1540–Male":"1540–Desede","1560–Male":"1560–Desede","1520–Male":"1520–Desede","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","about 1540":"about 1540"},"hu":{"about 1540–":"1540 körül–elhunyt","1540–Male":"1540–elhunyt","1560–Male":"1560–elhunyt","1520–Male":"1520–elhunyt","1520":"1520","1540":"1540","1560":"1560","about 1540":"1540 körül"},"id":{"about 1540–":"sekitar 1540–Telah Meninggal","1540–Male":"1540–TelahMenin